class Solution {
public:
    int appendCharacters(string s, string t) {
        int i = 0, j = 0;
        while (i < s.size() && j < t.size()) {
            if (s[i] == t[j]) j++;
            i++;
        }
        return t.size() - j;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n + m)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through both strings once, maintaining two pointers. When a match is found, it advances the pointer for string t. The remaining characters in t are the ones that need to be appended to s.

